<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Third session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b> China, Indonesia, Iran (Islamic Republic of)</b>&#8727;<b>, Japan, Nepal</b>*<b>, Pakistan,  
 Palestine</b>*<b>, Philippines, Republic of Korea, Saudi Arabia, Sri Lanka,  
  Syrian Arab Republic</b>*<b>:</b>  <b>draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b> 3/&#8230; Regional cooperation for the promotion and protection  
  of human rights in the Asian and Pacific region 
</b></p>
<p> The Human Rights Council, recalling resolution 2005/71 of 20 April 2005 of the 
Commission on Human Rights, decides to convene the next session of the Workshop on 
Regional Cooperation for the Promotion and Protection of Human Rights in the Asian and 
Pacific Region in 2007, preferably in the first half of that year. 
</p>
<p>----- 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p>&#8727;  Non-member States of the Human Rights Council. 
